meta-app
========

Application layer that packages the Qt-based head unit and instrument cluster
for the DES infotainment stack.

Provided recipes
----------------

* ``recipes-des/headunit/headunit.bb`` – builds the modular Qt head-unit UI,
  installs its assets, and drops ``headunit.service`` to launch it under Weston.
* ``recipes-des/instrument-cluster/instrument-cluster.bb`` – builds the Qt
  instrument cluster (`appIC`) from the external source tree and ships the
  matching ``instrument-cluster.service``.

External source layout
----------------------

Both recipes stage their sources from sibling workspaces so developers can keep
writing code outside Yocto:

* ``HEADUNIT_SRC ?= "${TOPDIR}/../../Head-Unit"``
* ``IC_SRC ?= "${TOPDIR}/../../DES_Instrument-Cluster/Cluster-app"``

Ensure the paths are accessible in your build environment or override them in a
``.bbappend``/``local.conf`` entry.

Integration
-----------

Add the layer to the build configuration:

.. code-block:: bash

   bitbake-layers add-layer meta-custom/meta-app

The image recipe ``meta-custom/meta-env/recipes-core/images/des-image.bb``
already depends on ``headunit`` and ``instrument-cluster``; custom images can do
so with:

.. code-block:: bitbake

   IMAGE_INSTALL:append = " headunit instrument-cluster "

Systemd units are enabled automatically on install.  Inspect their runtime state
with ``systemctl status headunit instrument-cluster`` on the target.
